
                        Section 2 - Notes
                      STOPSIGNAL Instruction

1.  Dockerfile in this directory.

    $ cat Dockerfile
    FROM ubuntu:trusty
    STOPSIGNAL SIGUSR1
    CMD ["/bin/sleep", "30"]

2.  Build image.

    $ docker build -t ss .

3.  Run detached ssc container.

    $ docker run -d --name ssc ss

4.  Verify container is running.

    $ docker ps -a
    CONTAINER ID   COMMAND           CREATED       STATUS       
    14b8c4b53b1f   "/bin/sleep 30"   2 weeks ago   Up 1 second

5.  Stop container.

    $ docker stop ssc
    ssc

    Signal SIGUSR1 sent to container.
    
